5751S06.02S
SENATE AMENDMENT NO. ___
Offered by Of
Amend SS/SCS/Senate Bill No. 1003 , Page 2 , Section 41.216 , Line 27 ,
2 by inserting after all of said line the following:
3 "41.430. 1. This section shall be known and may be
4 cited as "The Supporting Missouri Servicemen and Women Act".
5 2. Officers, warrant officers and enlisted personnel
6 of the organized militia on active duty in the service of
7 the state shall receive as compensation the same pay,
8 longevity, and allowances as are or may be provided for
9 members of like grade and branch of service in the Armed
10 Forces of the United States[.], except:
11 (1) Members of the organized militia serving on active
12 duty shall receive as a minimum the daily rate equivalent to
13 the grade level of E5 with maximum longevity and with
14 dependents;
15 (2) Members of the organized militia serving on active
16 duty in service of the state for more than thirty days shall
17 receive a monthly allowance for any premiums for coverage of
18 the member under the TRICARE program of the United States
19 Department of Defense or under any other government-
20 sponsored insurance program during the period of active
21 duty."; and
22 Further amend the title and enacting clause accordingly.
